   WHO'S NEWS: MCA Inc.'s Universal Studios unit said Linda
Berkeley was named to the newly created post of vice
president of business development. She will report directly
to MCA President Sidney Sheinberg. She worked for eight
months through October 1988 for Walt Disney Co., a major MCA
rival, as director of marketing resources and planning. . . .
Times Mirror Co. said Francis P. Pandolfi, president and
chief executive officer of Times Mirror Magazines, assumed
the additional new post of chairman of Sporting News
Publishing Co., whose publications include the Sporting News
and the Sporting Goods Dealer. . . . Ziff Communications Inc.
said its Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. unit named Eric Hippeau
executive vice president in charge of foreign and domestic
magazine operations. He was publisher of PC Magazine.
Ziff-Davis also said it will launch a magazine, PC Sources,
for mail-order microcomputer products. Last week, it said it
would create a book division, Ziff-Davis Press, to publish
computer books.
